<div class=3D"uw-text-block">
    <p>The <a href=3D"https://gpacalc.ls.wisc.edu/gpa-calculator/">GPA calc=
ulator link</a> on this page can help you understand how your academic stat=
us would be impacted by the grades you might receive in your current (or fu=
ture) courses. In order to use the calculator, you will need to know your c=
urrent academic status, your current grade point average (GPA), and your cu=
rrent GPA credits earned. You can find your current academic status on your=
 student record =E2=80=9C<a href=3D"https://registrar.wisc.edu/transcript/"=
>unofficial transcript</a>=E2=80=9C. Your current GPA and GPA credits earne=
d (=E2=80=9CGPA CRED. EARNED=E2=80=9D) can be found in your <a href=3D"http=
s://kb.wisc.edu/registrar/94069">DARS</a> within the section =E2=80=9CQUALI=
TY of WORK in the DEGREE.=E2=80=9D</p>
</div>
</div><div class=3D"uw-page-element uw-pe uw-pe-text_block" data-page-eleme=
nt=3D"text_block">
<div class=3D"uw-text-block">
    <h2>Cumulative GPA and Credits</h2>
<p>For best accuracy, please make sure you enter below your current <em><st=
rong>4-digit CUM GPA</strong></em> (e.g., 2.979, 3.200, etc.) that appears =
on your DARS or unofficial transcript when using the <a href=3D"https://gpa=
calc.ls.wisc.edu/gpa-calculator/">L&amp;S GPA calculator</a>.</p>
</div>
</div>            </div>
